free_txt: For Some Cases the Independent and Cumulative
Yields were Determined from Decay Curves.
Secondary Neutrons Influence Should Show Up Fully in
Cumulative Yield Determinations For Neutron-Rich
Isotopes Such As I-135. In the Case of Independent
Yield Determination, however, only the Independent
Yields from the Secondary Reaction Disturb. Since the
Energy of Most of the Neutrons is of the Order of a Few
MeV Only, these Independent Yields are Low and can be
Neglected - Estimated to be Less Than 1 % of the
Primary Yield For the Target Arrangement Used.
.Methane-Flow Proportional Counters.
.X-Ray Counter (THIN SCINTILLATOR).
.A Coincidence Counter Set to Detect
Annihilation Gammas from Positrons and a Scintillation
Spectrometer For Gamma Measurements.
.The Total Standard Deviation Including the
Calibration Errors in the Efficiency Factors and the
Error in the Monitor Reaction Cross Section.
.The Statistical Standard Deviation Showing
The Reproducibility of the Determinations.
Three Chemical Separation Methods were Used.
.At 590 MeV.
.At 18 GeV.
. Decay-Data from the
paper were used, unless denoted as 'from ENSDF'.
The Uranium Targets were Made of 47 Mg/Cm**2 or 94
Mg/Cm**2 Foils Mounted in a Stack with Three Aluminium
Foils on Each Side, the Middle Ones 0.01 mm and the
Others 0.03 mm Thick. The Middle Aluminium Foils were
Used As Beam Monitors.
The Lanthanum Targets were Made of 62 Mg/Cm**2 Foils
Mounted in a Stack with Three Aluminium Foils on Each
Side, the Middle Ones 0.01 mm and the Others 0.03 mm
Thick. The  Middle Aluminium Foils were Used As Beam
Monitors.
The Targets of Samarium were Powder Targets Consisting
Of Sm(2)O(3) And had a Thickness of 100-200 Mg/Cm**2.
The Targets of Cesium were Powder Targets Consisting
Of Cs-N-O(3), and had a Thickness of 100-200 Mg/Cm**2.
The Targets of Neodymium were Powder Targets Consisting
Of Nd(2)O(3) And had a Thickness of 100-200 Mg/Cm**2.
The Tantalum Targets were Made of 83 Mg/Cm**2 Foils
Mounted in a Stack with Three Aluminium Foils on Each
Side, the Middle Ones 0.01 mm and the Others 0.03 mm
Thick. The  Middle Aluminium Foils were Used As Beam
Monitors.
The Gold Targets were Made of 77 Mg/Cm**2 Foils
Mounted in a Stack with Three Aluminium Foils on Each
Side, the Middle Ones 0.01 mm and the Others 0.03 mm
Thick. The  Middle Aluminium Foils were Used As Beam
Monitors.
